Class SpecializationDepthTypeMirrorComparator

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.lang.SpecializationDepthTypeMirrorComparator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparator<TypeMirror>
public final class SpecializationDepthTypeMirrorComparator extends Object implements Comparator<TypeMirror>
A Comparator that partially orders certain kinds of TypeMirrors according to the depths of their specialization hierarchies such that subtypes precede supertypes.

This Comparator implementation is inconsistent with equals.

Author:
Laird Nelson

    • specializationDepth

      public final int specializationDepth(TypeMirror t)
      Returns the specialization depth of the supplied TypeMirror, which must be an array type, a declared type, an intersection type or a type variable.

      The specialization depth of the type representing java.lang.Object is 0.

      The specialization depth of an immediate subclass of Object is 1.

      The specialization depth of an immediate subclass of an immediate subclass of Object is 2. And so on.

      Parameters:
      t - a TypeMirror; must not be null; must be an array type, a declared type, an intersection type or a type variable
      Returns:
      0 or a positive int representing the specialization depth of the TypeMirror in question
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if t is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if t is unsuitable for any reason
